Download Jenkins war & Put it inside any folder.

Goto the Folder, which has jenkins.war->click on cmd on the path.
In Command prompt type, java -jar jenkins.war --httpPort=9092. Enter.
Note: Can give any port number.
The Command prompt will display, up & fully running.
Goto browser & Enter, localhost:9092.

Login using the admin us & password.
Password will be on the path --> C:\Program Files\Jenkins\secrets\initialAdminPassword.
UserName is Admin.Here is the Admin's password. 

Can create account & sign in asusual.

Account Creation,
C:\Users\Reshma S\.jenkins\Config.xml open in notepad++
  <useSecurity>true</useSecurity>  ---> Change false
  In chrome, Enter localhost:9092.
  Manage Jenkins->Configure Global security->Security Realm->Jenkinsâ€™ own user database enable Signup.
  Then Click on Signup...
  
  To Close Jenkins click on Ctrl+C in command prompt. It will display message as "Jenkins Stopped".
  
Restart - Do the close action & start action
